1:
In you, Yahweh, I take refuge;
\q let me never be put to shame.
\q

2:
Rescue me and make me safe in your righteousness;
\q turn your ear to me and save me.
\q

3:
Be to me a rock for refuge where I may always go;
\q you have given a command to save me,
\q for you are my rock and my fortress.

6:
By you I have been supported from the womb;
\q you are he who took me out of my mother's belly;
\q my praise will be always about you.
\q

10:
For my enemies are talking about me;
\q those who watch for my life are plotting together.
\q

12:
God, do not be far from me;
\q my God, hurry to help me.
\q

17:
God, you have taught me from my youth;
\q even now I declare your wonderful deeds.
\q

19:
Your righteousness also, God, is very high;
\q you who have done great things, God, who is like you?
\q

21:
May you increase my honor;
\q turn again and comfort me.
\q
